	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-DK-19430528_01.jpg"/>
			<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-642" type="subject">persecution</term> of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/732800/republic-of-bulgaria.html">Bulgaria</placeName></p>
			<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1007" type="subject">legation</term> has the honour of dispatching to
				the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-006627">Royal Ministry</orgName> a report received from the
				Consulate of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/727011/sofia.html">Sofia</placeName>, No. 56. of <date when="1943-05-28"> 28 May
					1943</date>, on the above-quoted topic.</p>
			<pb n="2" facs="EHRI-DK-19430528_02.jpg"/>
			<p>With reference to previous reports, the Consulate hereby has the honour to report that according to a regulation of the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-007263">Minister of the Interior</orgName>, published in the current <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1068" type="subject">Press</term> on the 25th of this month, all <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/727011/sofia.html">Sofia</placeName> must be <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1173" type="subject">moved</term> to the Province. As written in the
				Consulate's Report no. 94 from <date when="1942-09-01"> 1.9.1942</date> all unemployed <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> were to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-625" type="subject">leave</term>
				<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/727011/sofia.html">Sofia</placeName>. However, since only a few <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> have left <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/727011/sofia.html">Sofia</placeName>, the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-595" type="subject">Commission on Jewish Affairs</term> is now carrying
				out an expulsion. Every <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jewish</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">family</term> in Sofia is given a 3-day time limit
				to leave <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/727011/sofia.html">Sofia</placeName>, during which the provincial town is announced
				to which they have to relocate. Those <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term>
				who do not comply with this regulation will be <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-880" type="subject"
					>expelled</term> from the country immediately.</p>
			<p>About 23,000 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> are affected by this
				Regulation. In <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/727011/sofia.html">Sofia</placeName>, there are approx. 25,000 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term>, and only <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> who are <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1149" type="subject">foreign</term> nationals, and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> who are <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-488" type="subject">civilized mobilized</term> can still remain in
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/727011/sofia.html">Sofia</placeName>. In old <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/732800/republic-of-bulgaria.html">Bulgaria</placeName>, there are approx. 41,000 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term>, including 18,000 in the Province. About
				10,000 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> are mobilized, and the majority
				are <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-489" type="subject">employed</term> by <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">road construction workers</term>.</p>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_dr_biering_erik_andreas_mathias">Erik Andreas Mathias Biering</persName></p>
